-- Caterpillar CEO says U.S. probably in recession
-- 
-- Wed Mar 26, 2008 4:27am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/26/us-caterpillar-recession-idUSTKF00302520080326

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - The chief executive of Caterpillar Inc ( CAT.N ), the world's largest maker of earthmoving equipment, said the United States economy is probably in a recession but would likely recover from late this year. 

 Caterpillar Chairman and CEO Jim Owens made the comments at a news conference in Tokyo to announce that the firm was raising its stake in a joint venture with Japan's Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Ltd ( 7011.T ).